stories.title: How can a Scrum daily not be a status pull?

stories.text:
I usually find myself swinging between 2 moods; One is being productive, writing, shipping code, features, working on side projects...

At that time, I'll be also drinking, eating junk, tons of coffee, irregular sleep, staying inside for days, etc...

Then when I see that it is not very healthy, I will go to the gym, be regular, eat better and socialize. That leaves little to no energy to do more than minimum work.

It seems that I can't merge the good parts of each cycle and be social, healthy, while at the same time, productive and motivated.

Has anyone here been in this situation and figured their way out?
stories.title: Ask HN: Why does productivity and health feel diametrically opposed?

The space-to-product ratio effect: More space, more sales

stories.text:
I know Wordpress is a bit looked down on in HN circles, but there’s still nothing like it for building advanced websites for semi-pro developers like me.

However most functionality is provided by freemium plug-ins that often try to do way too much to justify the subscription.

I’m trying to build out a list of high quality open source plug-ins that provide essential functionality, as a contrast to the standard commercial model.

So HN, what are the free/libre Wordpress plug-ins that you can’t live without?
